Like a dream come through, Mrs Chikeluba Rita Isoken, who gained national popularity in 2009, as one of the participants in the popular Koko Mansion, a woman reality show in conjunction with Oladapo Daniel Oyebanjo, popularly known as DBANJ and the mo’hits crew is now talk show expert on marital issues and others. At the young age of 19, Rita, had taken special interest in societal issues with the dream and hope of offering solution. Little did she know then that 20 years down the line, she will be the producer host and anchor of a popular talk show with special focus in saving marriages and educating families on lasting relationships. Recall that Kokomansion show was designed to search and showcase the ideal woman that will be an epitome of a Nigerian marriage material. Leadership had last week chatted the mother of three, after many years where she talked about her present passion. “After the successful completion of the show in 2009, I decided to further my education which was most importantly the reason I went on the platform as I was unable to prior to the show because of my family dynamics” “Today, I am a well educated woman. I have achieved what can be described as “a grass to grace” status. “I currently have a platform to tell my story of a personal transformation via (ritaTV), a TV show where I motivate, inspire as well as encourage married couples and aspiring couples; even the singles will benefit from my story and experience. I am a wife and a proud mother of three amazing children.” When asked how she came about the idea of going into resolving marital issues, she said:  “The idea came to me in the bathroom. I think more when I am in the bathroom. My mission is to restore homes and God has been faithful.”  